## Content Guidelines

### Achievement Documentation
- **Specific Accomplishments**: List concrete deliverables and features
- **Technical Details**: Include performance improvements and optimizations
- **User Benefits**: Highlight user-facing improvements and capabilities
- **Metrics**: Include quantitative improvements and benchmarks

### Status Management
- **Current Status**: Always show current phase and next priorities
- **Completion Tracking**: Update percentages as work progresses
- **Milestone Dates**: Include completion dates for finished phases
- **Next Steps**: Clearly indicate what comes next

### Cross-Reference Integration
- **TODO.md**: Link completed tasks to their TODO.md origins
- **ROADMAP.md**: Connect achievements to roadmap phases
- **CHANGELOG.md**: Reference user-facing changes and improvements
- **Technical Architecture**: Note architectural improvements and optimizations

### Update Triggers
- **Milestone Completion**: When phases reach 100% completion
- **Weekly Updates**: Regular progress percentage updates
- **Achievement Unlocks**: When significant features or improvements are delivered
- **Status Changes**: When priorities or timelines shift

### Quality Standards
- **Accurate Percentages**: Keep completion status current and realistic
- **Detailed Achievements**: Provide specific examples of what was accomplished
- **Visual Clarity**: Use consistent formatting and visual indicators
- **Comprehensive Coverage**: Include all significant development milestones